<p>Sayori: (grinning) "No problem, Yuri! Plus, it's an opportunity for some quality bonding time."</p>
<p>(Natsuki and Monika share a small smile as they work side by side.)</p>
<p>Monika: "You know, cleaning up can actually be quite therapeutic. It gives us a chance to reflect and unwind."</p>
<p>Natsuki: (nods) "Yeah, you're right. I guess it's not all bad. And it does feel good to have a neat and organized space."</p>
<p>(After some time and effort, the clubroom starts to regain its tidiness.)</p>
<p>Monika: (admiring the room) "Well done, everyone. The room looks great again."</p>
<p>Yuri: (proudly) "We make a great team, don't we?"</p>
<p>Sayori: (happily) "Definitely! And thanks for not being too mad at me, guys."</p>
<p>Natsuki: (playfully) "Don't make a mess again, or else we'll have to start charging you a cleaning fee."</p>
<p>(Sayori laughs and pokes her tongue out at Natsuki.)</p>
<p>Monika: (smiling) "Alright, let's get back to our club activities and enjoy our time together as literature enthusiasts."</p>
<p>(The club members gather around the table, ready to continue their passion for literature in their now clean and organized clubroom.)</p></div>

