The financial performance of FindMyRoof will be evaluated using various financial ratios, including liquidity ratios, profitability ratios, and solvency ratios. Liquidity ratios measure the company's ability to meet short-term obligations. The current ratio shows the company's ability to pay current liabilities with current assets. FindMyRoof expects to maintain a current ratio of 2 or higher. Profitability ratios measure the company's ability to generate profits relative to sales or investments. The net profit margin ratio shows the percentage of net income generated from sales. FindMyRoof aims to maintain a net profit margin of at least 10%. Finally, solvency ratios measure the company's ability to meet long-term obligations. The debt-to-equity ratio indicates the proportion of debt financing to equity financing. FindMyRoof aims to keep the debt-to-equity ratio below 1.</p>
<p>Investment Strategies<br />
FindMyRoof plans to invest in several areas to support its growth objectives. The company plans to use most of its cash reserves to buy residential rental properties to generate rental income. FindMyRoof also plans to invest in technology to improve the user experience, such as developing a mobile app, upgrading the website, and using online marketing to increase its digital presence. Moreover, the company plans to expand its customer base by partnering with real estate agents and property owners. Finally, FindMyRoof intends to use some of the profits to reward its employees, expand its social responsibility initiatives, and increase the reinvestment in the business.</p>
<p>Conclusion<br />
The financial plan of FindMyRoof is designed to ensure the company's financial stability and support its growth objectives. The projected financial statements indicate that the company's revenues will steadily increase, leading to a positive net income in year two and three. The financial performance analysis highlights the need to maintain appropriate levels of liquidity, profitability, and solvency ratios. Finally, FindMyRoof plans to invest in several areas, including rental properties, technology, customer base expansion, and social responsibility initiatives.</p>
